{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[E5]  She stood there bright as the sun on that [A/E]California coast.
[D/E]  He was a Midwestern boy on his [E5]own.    [E5]
[E5]  She looked at him with those soft eyes, so [A/E]innocent and blue.
[D/E]  He knew right then he was too far from [E5]home.    [E5]

[E5]  Oh,  [A/E] he was too far from [D/E]home.   [E5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[E5]  She took his hand and she led him a[A/E]long that golden beach.
[D/E]  They watched the waves tumble over the [E5]sand.   [E5]
[E5]  They drove for miles and miles up those [A/E]twisting, turning roads.
[D/E]  Higher and higher and higher they [E5]climbed.   [E5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_chorus: Chorus}
And those Hol[E5]lywood nights
In those Hol[A/E]lywood hills
She was loo[D/E]king so right
In her dia[E5]monds and frills

Oh those b[E5]ig city nights
In those high[A/E] rolling hills
A[D/E]bove all the lights
She had all[E5] of her skills
{end_of_chorus}


