{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[E5]  He'd headed west 'cause he felt that a [A/E]change would do him good.
[D/E]  See some old friends, good for the [E5]soul.    [E5]
[E5]  She had been born with a face that would let [A/E]her get her way.
[D/E]  He saw that face and he lost all control.   [E5]

[E5]  Yeah,  [A/E] He had lost all [D/E]control.   [E5]
{end_of_verse}


{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[E5]  Night after night, day after [A/E]day, it went on and on.
[D/E]  Then came that morning he woke up alone.
[E5]  He spent all night staring down at the [A/E]lights of L.A.
[D/E]  Wondering if he could ever go [E5]home.
{end_of_verse}


